President Donald Trump spoke with President Recep Tayyip Erdogan of Turkey to reaffirm the strategic partnership between the two countries in combating terrorism and fostering regional stability. They discussed the importance of implementing United Nations Security Council Resolution 2254 and supporting the United Nations-led Geneva Process to peacefully resolve the civil war in Syria. They emphasized the need to end the humanitarian crisis, allow displaced Syrians to return home, and ensure the stability of a unified Syria free of malign intervention and terrorist safe havens. President Trump also informed President Erdogan of pending adjustments to the military support provided to partners in Syria, now that the battle of Raqqa is complete and the focus is on stabilization. The leaders also discussed the purchase of military equipment from the United States.